    • Constructor Detail

      • FileDialogFilter

        public FileDialogFilter(java.lang.String name,
                        java.lang.String[] extensions)
        Instantiates a new File dialog filter.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the filter.
        extensions - The extensions array. It should be formatted like { ".extension1", ".extension2", ... }. The extension can be like ".ext1.ext2". Use { "*" } for all types.

    • Method Detail

      • meetExtensions

        public boolean meetExtensions(java.lang.String filename)
        Check whether a file matches extensions.
        Parameters:
        filename - The filename to check.
        Returns:
        The value will be true if the extension of the file equals one of extensions, or false if the extension of the file equals nothing.

      • formatFilename

        public java.lang.String formatFilename(java.lang.String filename,
                                       int index)
        Format filename string.
        Parameters:
        filename - The original filename.
        index - The index in extensions. Accepts value that < 0 (will index from the end of extension). It will be reset to 0 if an invalid value passed in.
        Returns:
        The new filename string.
